reviews: This is a clean, comfortable modern hotel that could be a Hyatt anywhere in the world except that the rooms would be bigger in other cities. So it lacks character but will seem safe and familiar to the largely US clientele. I speak French but was always spoken to in English, which I find irritating. Can you not even say Bonjour when in Paris? My bed and breakfast were fully prepaid but my credit card was debited €100 per day at check in to cover incidentals notably mini bar use, I was told. There was nothing in the minibar. I'm not used to having to pay up front for stuff that I may or may not use and can only assume that this is Hyatt's way of dealing with cash flow problems. The money was refunded to my card soon after I left. On the plus side, the brasserie is excellent - great food and service, some of the best I've ever had in a Paris hotel.

I had high expectations for this hotel, they did not just live up to that, they even exceeded them. 
Great location, close to everything.The staff is super friendly, the best and kindest concierge ever. The room service staff was so nice and they delivered the food fast, warm and most importantly delicious. The suite is cosy and comfortable. The toilet seat has its own shataf (shower head). The ac was so efficient. The shower was spacious and enjoyable.
The view was great and we were able to enjoy entertainment from it. 
It is not the first hotel we stayed in, but is definitely the best.

The hotel is clean and well kept. The staff are very friendly. However, we found it challenging to get service if we needed assistance, such as room service or additional towels. Our room on our first day after an 8 hour flight was ready very late in the day -- after check in time which was supposed to be 4 p.m. Twice we returned to the hotel to find the doors closed with no exterior handle and no one there to open the door - we had to pry our fingers through the door jam to get it open so we could get into the hotel. For the price we paid - approximately 1,500 Euros/night, we expected much better service.

Incredible location, gracious staff, wonderful suite. I have stayed here every time I have visited Paris and highly recommend the Hotel du Louvre. This hotel delivers everything that a visit to Paris is supposed to provide.

We would definitely stay at this hotel again. The Lourve was right next door and most of the big sights were within walking distance. So many great restaurants right down the street. We could easily walk to the Champs Elysees to shop as well. They are very kind and helpful at the hotel and the food is excellent!

We were very happy with our stay at this property. The room was comfortable and the staff was attentive. Housekeeping was very attentive and we enjoyed the speedy room service. I would highly recommend it on location alone!

Everyone was helpful and friendly. An excellent place to stay, well maintained. First Class treatment by everyone. Just two blocks away from le musée du Louvre and le Carousel mall. I would definitely stay here again.

We have stayed at this hotel 4 times in the last 2 years and we have consistently had a great experience staying there. The staff are wonderful and attentive and ensure that all needs are met. The hotel is very well maintained and is a very comfortable place to stay. We had breakfast in the Brasserie each morning and the buffet was exceptional. This is a quality hotel and is not inexpensive but does represent great value for money.

We stayed 5 nights. We had breakfast included at their brassiere. There was a glitch with our room AC that couldn’t be fixed in a timely manner and the hotel changed our room the next day. For our trouble, they gave us a complimentary meal at the brassiere and apologized profusely. Everyone handling the situation was very polite, professional and efficient. Stuff happen, we all understand. This is a place that will work on your behalf to resolve unexpected issue PDQ, based on our experience. We highly recommend this hotel.

My adult daughter and I stayed at the Hotel du Louvre in May 2023 and we were pleasantly surprised at how wonderful our choice of hotels was!! The rooms were spotless and well cared for. We were greeted with a beautiful bottle of French wine and a bowl of fruit that carried us through the week. The bistro is a delicious option for breakfast and dinner. All of the restaurant, bar and hotel staff were the best! Very well trained and friendly. Be sure to call on the concierge! They are very helpful before your arrival by email and once you are on site. You will be so happy you selected Hotel du Louvre!!

We spent 5 days in Paris and this Hyatt by the Louvre was wonderful. Easy walking access to major sites and districts. Lots of cafes in neighborhoods. Room was lovely and with a walk in shower and staff was amazing. Always friendly and greeted with a smile. Mr. Alejandro at the front desk was always very helpful and went out of his way when needed. Would definitely recommend this hotel for a very comfortable stay in Paris.

This hotel is not inexpensive, but, in my opinion, worth the cost. It is very clean and modern, in a great location, has a very good restaurant, and there are a variety of dining options within walking distance. The staff is attentive and pleasant. I have stayed there on my last two visits to Paris, and I will likely stay there on my next visit.

I was at the Hotel du Louvre for business and a few days off. The service was superb, from start to finish. The location in the 1er Arrondissement is superb. The rooms are efficiently laid out and contained everything I needed for my travels. I would stay here again.

Our first stop in paris. What a wonderful place. Not mention the location, cross street of Museum du Louvre. All staff we met are greeting us with friendly smile.
The reception Clement is helpful, friendly and handsome. Manager, Francisco, provide us early check in and upgrade us to a suite with Museum Du Louvre view.
The server Benoit at the breakfast restaurant are passionate and attentive. All servers there are very friendly but I can’t name each of them.
And I want to give my highly appreciation to Gyaltsen who gave us warm welcome and took good care of our luggages when we check in. And he ran far from hotel to get taxi for us in the rain after we check out.
Over all, we had a wonderful experience at Hotel du Louvre from the moment we arrived till the minutes we got on taxi to next destination.

This hotel is located right across the street from the Louvre and down the road from the Opera/Palace Garnier. It has been entirely renovated and has one of the best staff we've ever found at a hotel. Built at the time of the World Exhibition that saw the construction of the Eiffel Tower, it has a rich history and you can get a guided tour of the hotel and environs if you schedule it with the concierge. The staff were incredibly efficient, positive and helpful. Very highly recommended!

Hotel is part of the Unbound Collection of Hyatt. Solid choice all around - rooms are nice, excellent service, great location. Dining is excellent too - nice cocktail bar (Officine du Louvre) and breakfast restaurant (Brasserie du Louvre-Bocuse)

We were pleasantly surprised by the nice condition of the room and related amenities, but at almost $2,000 per night, one would expect a better trained and staffed experience. One person at check-in, unmanned concierge desk, little concern for getting to guests all contributed to a much lesser experience, and suggests the property has a long way to go before it can compete with other premier properties.

Hotel du Louvre was an excellent choice for our First Time in Paris. The Location was perfect for our needs.
First Class service, Exception unique staff and a Positive welcoming hospitality sense.
Our Sincere compliments...Texas Style.

I, unfortunately, have a difficult situation to share that occurred at this hotel. From their response, I do not feel guest safety is taken seriously. We attended their hosted World Cup watch party during the 3rd day of our 4 night stay in a family room. Our family was seated in the last row in high top chairs behind a couch and in both ends of a serving bar. During the course of the event, a man from the party in front of us crossed me multiple times where there was no room to cross and plenty of wide open paths to cross the room in rows in front. After 2 times of him dragging himself across me, touching me, no excuse me’s while I’m trying to make myself smaller and smaller to avoid, I tell my husband that this is making me uncomfortable. We try to position ourselves to obstruct the crossing as a hint and he bulldozes over me pushing my legs away with his legs. He has been visiting the bar multiple times at this point and bringing the drinks to a party across the room and across us instead of having the servers deliver or going in the clear path in front. I leave the room and my husband says to him that he would appreciate him going around in the future as his passing is too close and disturbing to me. I return to the room. My husband updates me that they talked and the man had said Of Course. This is all happening within 2 feet of the bar area where there are about 20 hotel staff watching the game. Within 5 mins of me being back the man tries to come to me again. I’m there with my kids, it is a big game, and I’ve been hoping the direct reasonable approach discussion from my husband would cease his approaches. I am standing as the game is exciting and I’m attending to my children. There is not even 1 foot of distance between myself and the back of the couch. He proceeds to try to touch me and press himself against me again to “pass” again. I turned to him and I say No, there’s no more crossing here. My husband already talked to you and I am telling you I do not want you continuing to touch me while crossing me-there is no room here. He proceeds to look at me defiantly and then touch my belt buckle area five times. At which point, I raise my voice and I said stop touching me. I do not want you to touch me. Turn around and go back in front of the clear area in front of your family or I will call security. I know he was understanding me but he didn’t move and continued to look at me as if I was going to or should have acquiesced. So I turned my head to the left where a server noticed the commotion about a foot away and said Please call security. The lady came out, at this point the man hurried away to the front, she stopped him and said please don’t go through the back anymore, and came to me and essentially said let’s not make a scene. I held in tears through the rest of the game, while his family in front turned and verbally attacked us for yelling at him. Security never arrived. I tried to keep a brave face in front of the kids but it was disturbing to them to see this happen to their mom in front of them. We took a quick exit to dinner, and my husband went to the front to provide more details to the manager. We had several check-ins during dinner from the staff during which they said they take this situation very seriously and have had this type of complaint before and take it very seriously. Their gesture does not align with their words or their accountability in the setup, refusal to call security or discuss with me the events in the moment instead of telling me to not ruin the viewing. I have been affected by this series of events, unable to enjoy the rest of my stay at the hotel, this disgusting encounter in the back of my mind during the rest of the trip that completely affected my ability to relax and enjoy my family.

This hotel far exceeded our expectations! It's a perfect location, right in the center of all of the action. The rooms are spacious by European standards, and hotel is in excellent condition. Housekeeping, front desk, and concierge are all extremely helpful. We hope we can stay again in the future.

We just returned from an 8 night stay at the Du Louvre and the whole experience was great. A big shout out to the waiting team at their restaurant for impeccable service during our entire stay. The breakfast and the Christmas Eve dinner were wonderful . The concierge desk was very helpful in arranging for some last museum reservations and also some very good restaurant recommendations. We stayed in a connecting double room and the rooms are pretty big by European standards and housekeeping was available 24/7 to handle our requests. The location of the hotel is right next to the Louvre and other central attractions/shopping regions in Paris.

It would be great if they could add some more variety in their room service menu ( a bit more customisation if possible) and the daily breakfast menu. It gets a bit repetitive after 5-6 days.

Thanks to the Du Louvre for a memorable vacation.

I cannot say enough nice things about every person we met that works at the hotel - from those serving breakfast to those behind the front desk, they could not have been more helpful. We received an early check in, breakfast surpassed every expectation and was served by a widow with a view of the palais royale and when we asked for an extra converter we were handed one immediately. The room was spacious, and cleaned twice a day.

The service and stay at the Hotel du Louvre was amazing. We were in Paris for our honeymoon and it was completely magical. The hotel staff is welcoming & helpful, the hotel is beautiful, and it is located in a good area. It is around multiple landmarks to see with easy access to the metro. I highly recommend this hotel and thank them for being so awesome for my honeymoon.

Location was excellent for us .1 Block to Louvre Museum, walkable to St.Germain ,Palais Garnier, Place Vendome and many other attractions. Hotel was very clean, room had high ceiling and balcony.Breakfast at Brasseria was delicious. Hotel employees were beyond professional and helpful, especially Julien at concierge helped us tremendously, answered all our questions and gave us lots of recommendations. I already recommended this hotel to my family and friends. We'll definitely be back again .

Smell in the room was very bad. Bathroom ergonomy was pretty weird and uncomfortable. Location was fine although around the hotel was pretty dirty. For a 720 eur per night, value for money was way below expectations.

Enjoyed our stay. Staff were very welcoming, pleasant and helpful throughout our stay. Great location-close to restaurants and shopping and of course the Louvre. The rooms were very clean and kept up! Definitely recommend

The greatest Hyatt hotel taking care of Globalist that I ever been !

Hotel Du Louvre rescued us in chilly winter midnight!

Due to another 5 star hotel's lacking heating at midnight 11:30pm mid. November with unacceptable resolution, we miserably forced to new book room in midnight, we had to find warm and safe for current and next 2 nights. Luckily we found Hotel Du Louvre had available standard room for next 2 night. But how can we survived at present 11:35pm ?

We called Hotel du Louvre, the night shift supervisor Mr. Gxxx, picked up phone in no time. After listening my brief problem, He quickly keyed in system and said he found the room for us. He said " You can come any time " After half hour , we showed at lobby, he first sympathy my situation, greeted us welcome Hyatt Globalist, appreciate our loyalty,
then he offered us lrest at loft chair first. He's preparing room to check in soon.

Very soon, we were able to rest in room.

Thank you Hotel Du Louvre !

One of the best example of Hyatt Hotel taking card of Globalist in no time!

Hyatt Corp should be very proud of you.

Very nice hotel, rooms too small for the price and the internet was terrible. Well appointed hotel and staff are helpful and friendly.
Rooms are fine and clean, but to small, despite location being excellent and next door to the Louvre.

Hotel du Louvre did not disappoint in expectations of a high-quality, well-attended hotel. The staff were friendly, cleanliness was top-notch, and the central location was an added bonus. Check-in and check-out were very simple. This was our first stay in Paris, France and we will definitely choose this hotel again in the future.

My wife and I stayed here for three nights in November. We got in early, arriving at 12:30. I had checked in during our flight and the room was fortunately ready upon arrival since we were coming from the US. As expected the room was very nice but small. Basically the entire room was the bed with a little room on the sides and a couch in front of it. Even with that, there was decent closet space for our clothes.

Location was great. Our room looked out onto the Louvre and the window opened, which I imagine would be nice during warmer months. There's a metro stop right behind the hotel which was convenient, and lots of restaurants and attractions nearby. We did not eat at the restaurant in the hotel, but it looked nice.

I booked a six day trip to Paris at the Hotel du Louvre. My reservation was paid in advance. This morning ( 12/3/22) I received e-mail cancelling my reservation due to the hotel closing completely for renovations on January 8, 2023. I am shocked at this sudden action by the hotel.

Enjoyed our weekend stay at the Hotel du Louvre. Located right in the center of Paris. Easy walk to popular sights and good transport links. Clean and spacious rooms. Service was top notch. Breakfast was excellent. Great bar. What more could you ask for.

The location of this Hotel and its close proximity to The Louvre, Muse d'Orsay, The Opera House and Notre Dame which are all in easy walking distance makes this a perfect base to enjoy Paris. The extremely excellent Staff in the hotel at all levels make the stay so much more enjoyable. This is quality hotel in the PERFECT location.

Just completed an 8 night stay at this hotel for a mother daughter trip and could not have had a better experience!! We had a junior suite with a view, on the fourth floor overlooking the louvre. I think the hotel is not high enough to have such an incredible view since it’s 5 floors but it was nice to have given our long stay, we could look into the sculptures in the Louvre.

The room is massive and comfortable, with ample closet space for both of us. I appreciated the empty minibar so we could keep yogurts for breakfast and other snacks. The bathroom was great, with a lot of counter space and a strong blow dryer, along with a large shower and good water pressure.

Our room was not ready when we arrived early in the morning (we did get a text saying it was ready at 2pm which was nice), so they give you access to a private cabin that is basically like a large handicap bathroom with a shower and towels and soap. This was great to freshen up and change before we went out.

I also loved the room service - the bread basket with each meal is so tasty. We had a great breakfast one day and I ordered dinner several times after tiring days - the spaghetti bolognese was delicious. Not to mention room service is very affordable with no layers of extra fees! As a result we ordered 5+ times, each time costing a total of 20-30 euros.

The convenience of the hotel is great, there is a subway right outside so even on a rainy day you can get around easily. In theory you could get to the grand magasins by stepping out in the rain for 30 seconds. We also took the bus often so we could see the sights on the way to places.

Highly recommend Cafe Nemours across the street as a good nearby food option, as well as Franprix (get the activia muesli yogurt!) and Eric Kayser (great croissants and mixte sandwich) just a block away. My favorite new places during this trip to Paris were L’Oiseau Blanc (fancy restaurant), Le Compas (great cafe on rue montorgueil), and the department store BHV Marais!

We have had the fortune of staying at Hotel du Louvre. It is in a terrific location as it is walking distance to landmarks, museums etc. It is very central. The staff are wonderful, the restaurant and bar are great. The food here is some of the best we have eaten in Paris and it is an overall wonderful experience. Definitely recommend to anyone.

The location to restaurants, events, landmarks, museums, and the subway is unmatched. We were so pampered and it was luxury at its very best. From the super friendly concierge to the evening turndown service. Everything was top notch. Breakfast was amazing every day. It was hard to leave. We will be back!

Perfect location, especially for first timers in Paris. It's very central and walkable. The staff was great, very helpful - especially on our last day trying to get to the airport with a transportation strike happening. Hotel valet was able to hail us a cab at 7am on the street - which was not easy! Would definitely stay again; only downside is the room was crammed, but that's kind of expected in Paris.

The hotel staff was the best I’ve ever encountered while traveling in Europe. The breakfast and wait staff was amazing. The location is perfect to access all the main sightseeing in Paris. Plenty of great restaurants within walking distance and reasonably priced.

We stayed at the Hotel du Louvre for a week in November. We have stayed here countless nights over the past decade and it is truly our home away from home. The location and the quality of the accommodations are exceptional, only outclassed by the incredible service provided by the hotel staff. Fanny, the general manager of the hotel, always makes us feel sincerely welcome and is a wonderful representative of the hotel and of Paris. Upon arrival Francesco immediately greeted us and the entire staff made sure our experience was perfect. We can't wait to return. We would not consider staying anywhere else in Paris.

Great location! Stuff was friendly but room is a bit small. Walking distance to most major attractions. Louvre is only two minutes away. Lots of good restaurants are around the building. A little bit pricy but it is a five star hotel.

Situated very near to the Louvre Museum and therefore very convenient for other tourist attractions. A 5-star hotel, clearly better than 4-star hotels in the area, but you pay for it!
Well staffed. Personnel extremely attentive and helpful. Superb breakfast. Limited wardrobe space in our room.

The staff at the Hotel du Louvre are extremely helpful, the room comfortable and the food tasty. I enjoyed my stay completely. It is conveniently situated next to the Louvre and Metro stops for easy transit to other parts of the city, I highly recommend this hotel!

Staff was perfect! Breakfast is amazing and property is beatiful. The location is at The center of Paris, close to everything. The louvre is Just across The street. A lot.of.restaurants and cafés a short walk distante.

Overall good impression although I wouldn't rate it as a 5 star hotel,the breakfast was served at the brasserie the quality and the variety of choices were excellent .
In case you want to have your dinner in you have to go to brasserie again but since its open for the public also its not guaranteed that you will find a table,my opinion is that a five star hotel should give priority to paying guests,the food was excellent.The location is very convenient but very busy/noisy ,soundproofing wasn't up to the task and at times you might get annoyed by outside noise.
No spa and the bar even though was beautifully decorated it was very small in comparison with other establishments.

We had a a lovely spacious room with views of the Louvre. The public rooms, particularly the bar, are very attractive and the location is excellent. The staff were friendly and the service was good. My only criticism is that we could not get the AC to cool sufficiently.

We loved everything about this hotel! The included breakfast was above and beyond anything we’ve every experienced. Special shout out to Benoit at breakfast every morning! His smiling face and good demeanor we looked forward to each day.

Sadly the hotel was a disappointment for me due to a loud drumming noise in our room at night. The hotel itself is in an excellent location and has been recommended by a friend. The room was also lovely but the noise kept me awake all night and when we called someone up - he knew immediately it was the flagpole above our room (clearly I wasn’t the first to complain). the solution was for us to be moved the next night (I was staying only 1 night). In the morning I told the receptionist who couldn’t care less and simple asked ‘shall I use the card on file’. Rude. Sadly I will never return and I definitely wouldn’t recommend

We loved our trip to Paris and especially the Hotel du Louvre. The hotel is beautiful and the staff was friendly and attentive. The location is right across from the Louvre and the Orsay Museum was right on the other side of the Seine so you couldn't beat the location.

Cannot recommend
You hear and feel trains underneath hotel, impossible to find sleep
Location is good
Service okay
Restaurant good
Room size okay, clean
Noise from trains can be heard even on fourth floor
Also vibrations can be felt

We booked this hotel for a short family break with our two children. It’s a great location close to the Louvre. The staff were all very friendly and helpful. We all
enjoyed the breakfast here especially the French toast !
It’s a busy hotel and we did sneak in for desserts in the evening too but I would recommend to book as seems popular with locals aswell as tourists.

Our room was cosy but still good wardrobe space, bathroom / shower fine , clean and good standard… kids liked the bunk beds.

We would love to stay here again maybe for a trip in the future as a couple but also great for all the family :)

We selected the hotel for the proximity to the museums. It was easy to walk everywhere from this location to see all the major sites in Paris. It was also close to a taxi stand if we chose not to walk.
Concierge emailed us ahead of our trip to help offer any assistance in planning our stay. We had a 2 twin bed room that had an amazing view of the Opera house. The bar had amazing drinks and the restaurant had such good food we ate a few breakfasts, a lunch and a couple of dinners there when we were not out about the city at outside cafes.

This hotel is in need of a major renovation. Public spaces, carpets, and some furnishings are very dated and worn. The staff was helpful and the breakfast was great. The location is its greatest asset, but we would not stay there again. Not up to the Hyatt standard I expect.

Stayed 1 week and enjoyed it. Excellent location for tourist with 2-min walk to Louvre & metro, 15-min walk to Orsay. Best continental breakfast ever had with many hot dishes from kitchen. Besides, hotel staffs are nice and helpful as usual in Hyatt properties. Standard room is very very small however considering its expensive room rate, but it is well stated during reservation so I have no complains.

Our corner room at this hotel was beautiful, spacious and looked out at the Louvre and a cafe across the street. The bathroom was large with a fantastic shower, slippers, body lotion and other lovely amenities. The location was perfect, around the corner from the Louvre and the Jardin du Tuileries, across the street from Jardin du Palais Royal, 10 minute walk to Paris Opera House, and convenient to several nice cafes. There is a lovely bar and lounge in the lobby which is a nice place to relax and have a drink. Excellent restaurant on the premises. Highly recommend!

We spent a week in Paris at this Hotel. We felt very well taken care of. We had a great room, very clean, and great view of the city. The hotel is in a great location, very close to everything. We will for sure stay at this hotel again when we are in Paris.

The Hotel was BEAUTIFUL. It was clean and very well maintained. They knew it was our anniversary so in our room upon arrival they had a dessert and a bottle of french lemonade waiting for us. They also upgraded us to a King Delux. The bathroom was huge, marble and lovely. We definitely enjoyed our stay and would book again. The staff was extremely friendly. The only downside is breakfast is 30 euros pp a day. The Bakerys around were less than 5 eyros for a decent breakfast. Hyatt should offer breakfast to their CC holders.

Obviously, given that this grand hotel is literally next to the famous Louvre museum, it’s going to be pricey. But it’s worth it. Bright clean modern feel to the hotel unlike some grand hotels that feel shabby. Rooms are clean and fresh and well equipped. Mine was fortunate to have a balcony which added another delightful dimension.
The staff are attentive polite and room service is quick, although expensive.
Highly recommended for central location.

We just completed a 6 day visit to Paris at the Hotel du Louvre and the experience was superb. Our room (a Palais Royale suite on the 4th floor) was wonderful---a great view, quiet and peaceful in the midst of this busy city, and it reflected the understated elegance of the Hotel. The staff were remarkably warn, gracious, and helpful. The Brasserie du Louvre was great for breakfast and dinner---excellent foo and the wait staff shared the same warmth and grace of the hotel staff. We have stayed in other 5 star hotels in Paris but the Hotel du Louvre is simply the best. It feels like our home-in-Paris and we can't wait to go back.

On our final stop of a fantastic Post-COVID trip that took us through Hungary, Slovakia, Austria, Germany, and France -- LaCite was a fitting culmination before returning to Amerika. We've stayed in some lux hotels in our travels and HdL certainly ranks in our top five. The location, the friendly and helpful staff, the room presentation, the cozy bar, and a delicious breakfast made our stay quite memorable. A bit on the pricy side but worth every bit. Within walking distance to most of the important sites and access to the metro or taxi/riseShare access -- transportation was no issue. This will be a go-to spot to stay in future visits to LaCite.

Location is superb. The rest is a disappointment. This hotel holds a 5-star, special Hyatt Unbound Collection designation. I saw none of that. Nothing special. Utterly routine. Hallways worn and torn, some rooms shabby and odors wafted out of bathrooms. Staff is young and performs only the basic level of service. No grace here. Safe, towel warmer and coffee maker all broken.

The staff were lovely, the location fabulous, the rooms clean and bright. But this hotel is way overpriced. My room suffered from a lot of street noise and thin doors that rattled and banged whenever neighbouring guests opened and closed doors. I didn't sleep well. The decor was plain and corporate, everything looked a bit tired. I paid 900 euros for the night, excluding breakfast - OK it was Fashion Week - but I was expecting a very different experience. The brasserie and bar were beautiful and had great ambience, but the food was not to our taste, very heavy and rich, and the cocktails in the bar were so-so

Great location. Rooms were very clean and the staff were very friendly. Concierge was very helpful in getting us tickets to the museums and making dining reservations. We had a wonderful stay! Highly recommend.

You are paying for the location and a relatively large room in Paris. If this is your priority, this will be a good fit! In a Hyatt I expect consistently helpful staff and a good nights sleep but unfortunately I found neither of those in this hotel.

Fantastic location , walking distance to everything…. this intimate hotel is a great place to stay in Paris . Staff are great , rooms well designed and spotless , excellent breakfast .. overall a quality experience

We stayed at the Hotel du Louvre for 5 nights in September 2022, as part of our honeymoon. Overall, it was a very good stay.

The hotel’s location is excellent for sightseeing. Right by the Louvre obviously, but several other attractions are within walking distance: Opera Garnier, Musée D’Orsay, Centre Pompidou, Champs Elysées, among many others. And there’s easy access to the metro as well.

The building was tastefully renovated relatively recently. We appreciated the décor, that gave the hotel a sense of place and history but wasn’t at all tacky. They tried to go for understated luxury and really hit the spot!

Due to my Hyatt Globalist status, we were upgraded to a junior suite. It’s not a “traditional” suite, i.e. there’s no separation between bedroom and living room, but it was significantly larger than the base level rooms – which was greatly appreciated. Our room faced an internal courtyard so street noise was not an issue. Everything was in good working order as well, and toiletries and bedding were of good quality.

Also because of my Globalist status, breakfast was included in our rate. The buffet spread wasn’t particularly large but all items were of high quality – and made-to-order eggs could also be ordered too.

Service at both the restaurant and the front desk was professional and polished – nothing to complain here.

One thing to notice though: when housekeeping provided turndown service, they only left one small box of chocolates on the bed – and always very clearly by my (man’s) side of it, which annoyed my wife. Placing it at the centre of the bed would be a more polite and modern solution.

Fabulous location, dedicated and courteous staff, comfortable room & amenities! We couldn't have asked for more at this fantastic hotel! Would highly recommend to anyone! Bellstaff exceptionally attended to our needs with ubers/taxi//drivers.

Located steps from the center of the city, this hotel does not disappoint. The staff offered exceptional service and were friendly and professional. Room service delivered delicious coffee and the restaurant served us a delicious meal one evening when we decided to stay in. The room was pleasant and roomy with built in cabinets that gave us enough room to unpack completely. Would definitely stay there again.

Very central location right across the street from the Louvre and above the metro station. Room was very small, but to be expected for Paris. Overall it was a nice stay, but I would’ve been disappointed in the value of it had I not used Hyatt points; since the nightly rate was around 600 Euros.

Clean, great hotel staff, convenient location. Bar, restaurant, housekeeping, all respectful and helpful. Outside is a busy area, across from The Louvre. No noise in the room .Shopping and cafes nearby. We'll be back.

Wonderful service before we arrived and throughout our stay - helped coordinate and make reservations. Very kind staff, perfect location! No complaints, exceeded expectations. Will be staying with them from now on!

I highly recommend this hotel. Everything is walking distance,,, Louvre, museum de orsy, Tulleries gardens, Chamos de Elysse, tons of wonderful cafes, high end shopping in Vendome area and more!!! Also all the metro stations are within walking distance so you can take the metro to Versailles and other places easily! This hotel is nice also because you don’t need to get on a cab to go places. Also Notre Dame is within walking distance. Eiffel Tower is very close by cab as well as the Catacombs!

we have had the pleasure to stay at the magnificent HOTEL DU LOUVRE IN PARIS.
After having travelled the world for decades and seen many 5 star Hotels, well this one TOP 3 WORLWIDE. 5 star staff in whole of the hotel. Exceptional location. Phenomenal attention to details. Outstanding food and the view of the rooms very Paris.
This will be our forever Hotel in Paris. Thank you Hotel du Louvre.
D. Niedermann

In Paris for a week and had a great stay. the Louvre is right next to the hotel and our balcony gave us a great view. Check in was friendly and efficient and the hotel overall was perfect. We did a lot of sight seeing so we didn't spend a ton of time here but we enjoyed the friendly staff and very good breakfast everyday. We would absolutely stay here again and highly recommend it.

Hôtel du Louvre exceeded our expectations! For a first trip to Paris, we couldn’t have asked for a better location. There was a metro stop directly next to the hotel and endless restaurants and cafes to choose from within walking distance.

All good, great location, attention to details and accommodations for my wife in wheelchair . Room service at breakfast was very good and kudos to the bellman on arrival and departure.
Highly recommend this hotel

True 5 star hotel in Paris. Great service from house keeping, bellman, check in. Great location, walking distance to most attractions and shopping. Great restaurants nearby. Hotel restaurant for dinner room service was fantastic.

The hotel is extremely well located and is round the corner from the louvre. The building is stupendous and the hotel very grand. Rooms are comfortable and command excellent views. Breakfast is sumptuous. I definitely recommend this hotel.

An exceptionally well run hotel. We were on the fence. My wife was a travel photographer who shot for the likes of Conde Nast Traveler years was not sure it was charming enough. We have been all over the world and staying in some amazing properties. We were taking our 15 year old to France for the first time. He too has been all over the world and stayed in amazing places. Luxury is must for him - he is quite spoiled.

I am not sure I will ever be fortunate enough to stay in a Palais Royal Suite again for a 6 night stay. We have been to Paris many many times and have have never had a view like that. A fifteen year old stands on the balcony as the Tour Du France goes by. I will pine for it next time. It is not cheap but in my estimation its a great value. We have friend who was staying at famous hotel on Place Vendome in a room similar to ours & it must have been 3 or 4 times as much.

The service was exceptional. Ryan (fabulous) the concierge sorted 8 or so restaurant reservations before we arrived. Ice for drinks was delivered immediately and never ever required a second call. My wife was ill and when the room service waiter came with toast he said that the she needed tea and quickly returned with pot w/o a charge. It was quite charming.

The breakfast was great with a big selection my only complaint is the croissants should have been better. Dinner was fine we only ate there once on the night we arrived.

The location cant be beat - I like to stay in the thick of things and we typically stay in the 1st or 2nd in Paris. But this was the best location in my experience. Having the Metro next to the hotel is brilliant. I like to rent a Vespa and there is scooter parking is across the street.

It clean, comfortable the bathroom was great. The staff is friendly and out going very helpful.

Full disclosure: When we arrived they put us in room on the 5th floor (might have been 4) the ceiling was low I could touch it with flat feet and the windows were small. they moved us right away but had nothing else been available and I was paying what I paid for that room I probably would have checked out asap - leaving a very different review.

I am not sure I could go back if I could not have that view. It was a magical experience and one that cannot be replicated. Still I would not hesitate to stay here again. On a low floor. It met with our 15 year olds approval. As I said they ruined Paris it can never be the same again.

We stayed here as a family of 6, so we took 2 rooms. Our whole experience was amazing. The reception and concierge staff always attended to our needs, and went the extra mile to ensure we got what we are looking for. Looking forward to come back.

A romantic nice hotel located in a quite and modern area! Walking distance to the nicest shopping area! Wonderful buildings surrounded ❤️! Dinner in the hotel Brasserie was incredible good and a wonderful service!

This was a quick trip to Paris. This hotel was recommended by a friend. We were pleasantly surprised. Staff was very friendly and helpful. Room was clean and welcoming. I had a nice view from my room as well. Slept really well. Breakfast was great. It was wonderful. I will be back.

The hotel is in desparate need of an update. The hotel was rundown with chunks of paint missing from the walls and door frames and the room itself had a horrible stale smell. The staff was ok at best. The restaurant was good we had dinner there one night - food was tasty. My thoughts are if you are spending close to $800 a night the place should be a little nicer. A can of paint, spackle and some airfreshners and grout cleaner would go a very long way......

After an unpleasant experience at another local hotel we booked same day based upon online reviews, which turned out to be the highlight of our trip and the best vacation we could have asked for. The staff was welcoming and efficient and gave my wife and I a room with a direct view of the opera, which was room 206. The hotel has an amazing location in the center of everything and just steps to the Louvre and Jardins de Tuilleries. The property has a boutique feel and is modern yet classical French. I would highly recommend this property to anyone based upon the location, amenities, charm, cleanliness and overall condition of the property and attention to detail.

Usually I do not write such a big review, however they deserve it...

This was a family vacation with my wife and daughter. This Hotel scores five stars all the way. It all started the day i checked in , I had requested an early check in and we arrived at 9:00 am approximately. My room was ready and we were upgraded ( was based on availability ) they did not make any excuses , in fact they were true to their word. I still remember , Amale, at the reception was great!

The Concierge was excellent, the team which included Erick , Jillian , they made reservations for impossible places and also request for a hair parlor for my daughter on a Sunday evening. they made arrangements, when everything was closed.
Breakfast spread and the host and the team was excellent. loved it.
Not to mention the location , This location has it all and provides the charm of being in Paris.
This hotel is a great property. if you have any requests with them, if possible they will make it Happen.

This was our second time at the hotel and we loved it again. Staff is very attentive and professional. The location is unbeatable, a stone’s throw away from the Louvre museum. The food at the brasserie is great and the service is impeccable.

This hotel is a great mix of French charm and American conveniences. Since it is a Hyatt you know you will have expected amenities- like comfortable beds, good water pressure, strong air conditioning but American chain hotels can often lack character. This hotel feels very french and is very beautiful and charming. Great location for sight seeing and the metro stop is right next to the hotel.

This was my second stay at Hotel de Louvre. The first was several years ago. It was wonderful then and outstanding this time. The customer service is incredible. The staff often went well out of their way to make things more enjoyable. The restaurant staff new what coffee to bring me for breakfast after the first day. They treated me like an old friend. I took a travel group of 28 people and everyone had a wonderful experience. The concierge desk handled all of my clients needs with ease, suggesting and reserving reservations at area restaurants, provided excellent directions, helped get them in taxis and answered every question with a smile. I have stayed in other lovely Paris hotels. After this great visit, I will stay at Hotel de Louvre every time. It's like coming home to a house full of friends that are so glad you are home.

Had a wonderful stay at the Hotel Du Louvre. It was our honeymoon and they made us feel completely welcome. The room was small, but we had a wonderful view of the Louvre. It was in close proximity to many of the most popular sites and restaurants in Paris. Looking forward to visiting again in the future.

I stayed at the Hotel De Louvre for the final day of the Tour De France. Beautiful Hotel, great location, super clean, very friendly staff and an awesome breakfast. On arrival the staff were very efficient and polite. When i lost my hat and glasses they were very kind and helpful to find my belongings.

The staff were on top of my every request ! It was right next to meteo 1 and easy to get everywhere. The concierge reserved a taxi for me one morning. Room service took no longer than 30 minutes and in most cases much quicker. There is a lovely bar downstairs, the air conditioning worked perfectly during the hotest day on record !

Recent renovations have really made this hotel exceptional. Its location, right next to the Louvre museum & the Tuileries Garden, is extremely convenient. Plus, there's a genuine Paul Bocuse Brasserie on the first floor, with great food & service.

This hotel exceeded my expectations. I have stayed at other 5-star hotels in Paris and this one is the absolute best by far. From the exceptional hotel staff to the convenient location to the overall comfort of the rooms. Just wonderful!

This beautiful hotel is situated in a prime Paris location across the street from the Louvre. Room was spacious and very clean. Staff was very attentive and helpful. Bar is not to be missed. Has a fantastic stay. Highly recommend.

We stayed three days with my husband in July in a Deluxe view room and we could not be happier. Room was great and very cosy, all employees were extremely kind, breakfast was delicious (you should try the French toast - the best we have ever had)! We loved every minute of our stay. We cannot wait to return. Kudos to the management and merci!

It was nice to find a family suite with 2 guaranteed connecting rooms. The rooms were clean and well stocked. I found it odd that that the King room and bathroom (for the parents) was much smaller than the room with 2 twins (for the kids).
The location of the hotel was ideal for us to feel centralized to the main tourist attractions and metro. Although, the outside noise level while trying to sleep was disturbing at times. I was very disappointed with the doorman’s ability to secure us a taxi at times. When I tried to get one myself, he sent the taxi driver away (speaking in French so I did not understand) and did not explain to me why…just shrugged. We also asked the concierge to reserve a car service for us to the airport the night before leaving and was told to just use Uber. Was not impressed with the lack of 5 star service I had expected.

Great hotel, staff super friendly. They went out of their way to help. Hotel is very beautiful. Would Definitely recommend and would without a doubt stay again. Breakfast was great and reasonably priced. Location could not be better.

great location but horrendous hotel inside.... needs a complete refurb throughout...... the most overpriced hotel (1000 euros a night!) I have ever been in and one of the smallest hotel rooms in Paris! I will never be back to this hotel and recommend you avoid at all costs

Hotel du Louvre is beautiful, clean and in the best location. Our family of 5 was in one of their family suites. Rooms are beautiful, amazing views, so clean and comfortable. We had lots of space and bathrooms to all get ready at the same time and enjoy the sites. The Louvre is across the street, we walked mostly everywhere: Orsay, l'Orangerie, Jardin des Tuileries to Place de la Concorde, Champs Elysees, Arc de Triomphe... Getting to Eiffel is very easy as well. Walking in the other direction is Opera Garnier, and more shopping at Galleries Lafayette and Printemps.. I could go on and on we are so happy with the location. All staff are extremely attentive, they helped us with taxis, airport transportation, made sure the room was always stocked with coffee, water and toiletries. The food is also outstanding at the hotel, and the many restaurants very close by. Oh - also, the gym!!! Couldn't believe the view, floor to ceiling windows, all equipment is modern and in perfect condition, water bottles, towels and sanitizing wipes always available. We have no negatives - Hotel du Louvre is the best!!!

Great location near the Louvre with lots of cafes nearby and the Opera House down the street. Beautiful room. Helpful staff. Food is okay and pricy for the quality. Take a stroll to one of the bridges to watch the sunset over the Seine. It’s gorgeous!!

Best service that was a surprise, I mostly like to stay at the Mercredi; however, I was surprised at the extraordinary attention to detail and specifically at the best Onion Soup we, my wife and I, have ever tasted.
